THIS IS THE STORY ABOUT RONALD CLARK.
HE GREW UP RELATIVELY POOR BUT HE WASN'T AWARE HE WAS POOR.
THE STORY BEGINS WITH HIM SITTING AT THE DINNER TABLE WITH HIS PARENTS AND MAKING THE STATEMENT "WE ARE RICH.
HIS FATHER IS FLABBERGASTED BECAUSE THEY ARE NOT RICH.
RONALD CLARK'S FATHER WAS A LIBRARY JANITOR.
RONALD WOULD SPEND A LOT OF TIME AT THE LIBRARY.
HE WAS EMBARRASED AT FIRST BY THIS BUT GREW TO LOVE IT.
HE WOULD SPEND HOURS IN THE LIBRARY READING AND REASEARCHING ANYTHING.
HIS FATHER TOOK A LOT OF PRIDE IN HIS WORK AND THE LIBRARY HE CLEANED WAS ONE OF THE CLEANEST.
RONALD CLARK WAS ONE OF THE FIRST PEOPLE IN HIS FAMILY TO GRADUATE FROM COLLEGE.
HE WAS HIRED AT A COLLEGE.
HE BROUGHT HIS FATHER TO SEE HIS CLASSROOM ONE DAY.
HIS FATHER WAS VERY PROUD OF HIM, EVEN THOUGH HE WAS A STOIC MAN AND WOULD NEVER SAY IT OUT LOUD.
THE VIDEO WAS ANIMATED AND HAD MUSIC IN THE BACKGROUND.
IT WAS NARRATED BY A MAN WHOM I ASSUME WAS RONALD CLARK.
THE STORY WAS ABOUT RONALD CLARK.
HE WAS NARRATING THE STORY (OR SO IT SEEMED TO BE HIS VOICE).
THE STORY WAS ABOUT HOW HE VALUED HIS UPBRINGING.
HIS FATHER WAS A LIBRARY JANITOR AND HE WOULD SPEND A LOT OF TIME IN THE LIBRARY READING AND RESEARCHING BOOKS.
HIS FATHER TOOK GREAT PRIDE IN HIS JOB.
HE WOULD WAX EVERYWHERE IN THE LIBRARY, INCLUDING THE TOPS OF THEBOOSHELVES.
RONALD WOULD NEVER INVITE FRIENDS TO COME OVER TO HIS HOUSE.
NO ONE IN RONALD'S FAMILY HAD EVER GONE TO COLLEGE.
RONALD WENT TO COLLEGE AND EVENTUALLY BECAME A PROFESSOR AT A COLLEGE.
HE TOOK HIS FATHER TO SEE HIS CLASSROOM ONE DAY.
HIS FATHER DIDN'T SAY MUCH, AND INSTEAD WAS QUIET.
RONALD KNEW HE WAS PROUD THOUGH.
RONALD DIDN'T REALIZE HOW POOR HIS FAMILY WAS UNTIL THEY TOLD HIM.
HE LIVED WITH HIS FATHER AND MOTHER.
